article.headline: Hawaii 50, Fairfield 49 (OT)
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Julian Sensley sank a 3-pointer with 11 seconds left to lead Hawaii to a 50-49 overtime victory over Fairfield in the championship game of the Rainbow Classic on Tuesday night. Michael Kuebler added 22 points for the Rainbow Warriors (8-2) and was named the tournament's MVP. Sensley's game winner from the left side was his only 3-pointer of the night and gave Hawaii its second lead of the game. He finished with 12 points and 12 rebounds. Fairfield (7-2) had a chance to win the game, but Terrence Todd's shot clanked off the rim as time ran out. Deng Gai led the Stags with 17 points and 18 rebounds while DeWitt Maxwell added 10 points. Hawaii trailed by 10 early in the second half, but closed out regulation with an 8-0 run to force overtime. The run was capped by Phil Martin's layin with eight seconds that tied the game at 42. The Rainbow Warriors held the Stags scoreless in the final 3:11 of regulation. Fairfield jumped out to a 6-0 lead to start the game and then both teams went cold. Hawaii started the game shooting 1-of-16 from the field and finished the half making 4-of-25 shots. For the game, Fairfield shot 31 percent (21-of-68) while Hawaii shot just 29 percent (17-of-59). It was the third consecutive Rainbow Classic victory for Hawaii and its second straight overtime win. ------ Notes: Next year's Rainbow Classic field was announced Tuesday night. The teams are Hawaii, UAB, Clemson, Georgetown, Indiana State, Long Beach State, LSU and Southern California.
